<DOC><DOCNO>WSJ910905-0070</DOCNO><DOCID>910905-0070.</DOCID><HL>   Business Brief -- Brasfield andamp; Gorie Inc.:   OSHA Levies Record Fine   For Southeast on Contractor</HL><DATE>09/05/91</DATE><SO>WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), PAGE A2</SO><CO>   LABOR</CO><MS>INDUSTRIAL (IDU)</MS><IN>HEAVY CONSTRUCTION; INDUSTRIAL AND COMMERCIAL (CON)</IN><NS>LABOR, PERSONNEL ISSUES, TRENDS, MANAGEMENT TECHNIQUES (LAB)</NS><GV>LABOR DEPARTMENT (LBR)</GV><RE>ALABAMA (AL)NORTH AMERICA (NME)UNITED STATES (US)</RE><LP>   An Alabama contractor faces a fine of $580,000 fromfederal officials for alleged construction violations.   The Occupational Safety and Health Administration saidBrasfield andamp; Gorie Inc., based in Birmingham, Ala., failed totake adequate steps to protect 10 workers operating in a12-foot-deep excavation. The walls lining the side of thetrench, the federal agency said, were in danger of collapse.</LP><TEXT>   The proposed fine, which the company has 15 days tocontest, is a record for the Southeast, the agency said.   Officials at Brasfield andamp; Gorie were unavailable forcomment.</TEXT></DOC>